set -e
Script stops at error

set -u
Forces bash script to stop 
Stopped at undefined variable 

set -x
Prints each command before it is executed 
Set +x to stop it 

set -eux
use all 3 at once

Set –o nounset = set-u uninitialized variables 

 

Set –o errexit = -e exit if any invoked command fails nonexistent command 

 

Set –o pipefail = causes pipeline  to return the exit 
status of the last command in the pipeline that exited
with a non-zero status. 


